Document: MobileVRInterface
Path: godot/classes/class_mobilevrinterface.rst
Summary: Provides an interface for mobile VR devices.

Inherits: VRInterface < Object

This class provides an interface for mobile VR devices. It is the base class for mobile VR interfaces, such as Google Cardboard.

Key Rule: Mobile VR interfaces are typically implemented by third-party SDKs and are not part of the core Godot engine.

This class defines the basic methods and properties that a mobile VR interface must implement. These include methods for initializing and shutting down the VR session, getting the display capabilities, and handling input events.

The specific implementation of a mobile VR interface will depend on the target platform and VR SDK. For example, a Google Cardboard implementation would use the Cardboard SDK to interact with the device's sensors and display.

Note: Developers should consult the documentation for their specific mobile VR SDK for details on how to integrate it with Godot.
