Document: MobileVRInterface
Path: godot/classes/class_mobilevrinterface.rst
Summary: Properties for configuring the Mobile VR Interface, including display dimensions, lens properties, eye height, and Variable Rate Shading (VRS) settings.

Property Descriptions
Property: display_to_lens (float)
Default: 4.0
Setter: set_display_to_lens(value: float)
Getter: get_display_to_lens() -> float
The distance between the display and the lenses inside of the device in centimeters.

Property: display_width (float)
Default: 14.5
Setter: set_display_width(value: float)
Getter: get_display_width() -> float
The width of the display in centimeters.

Property: eye_height (float)
Default: 1.85
Setter: set_eye_height(value: float)
Getter: get_eye_height() -> float
The height at which the camera is placed in relation to the ground (i.e. XROrigin3D node).

Property: iod (float)
Default: 6.0
Setter: set_iod(value: float)
Getter: get_iod() -> float
The interocular distance, also known as the interpupillary distance. The distance between the pupils of the left and right eye.

Property: k1 (float)
Default: 0.215
Setter: set_k1(value: float)
Getter: get_k1() -> float
The k1 lens factor is one of the two constants that define the strength of the lens used and directly influences the lens distortion effect.

Property: k2 (float)
Default: 0.215
Setter: set_k2(value: float)
Getter: get_k2() -> float
The k2 lens factor, see k1.

Property: offset_rect (Rect2)
Default: Rect2(0, 0, 1, 1)
Setter: set_offset_rect(value: Rect2)
Getter: get_offset_rect() -> Rect2
Set the offset rect relative to the area being rendered. A length of 1 represents the whole rendering area on that axis.

Property: oversample (float)
Default: 1.5
Setter: set_oversample(value: float)
Getter: get_oversample() -> float
The oversample setting. Because of the lens distortion we have to render our buffers at a higher resolution then the screen can natively handle. A value between 1.5 and 2.0 often provides good results but at the cost of performance.

Property: vrs_min_radius (float)
Default: 20.0
Setter: set_vrs_min_radius(value: float)
Getter: get_vrs_min_radius() -> float
The minimum radius around the focal point where full quality is guaranteed if VRS is used as a percentage of screen size.
Note: Mobile and Forward+ renderers only. Requires Viewport.vrs_mode to be set to Viewport.VRS_XR.

Property: vrs_strength (float)
Default: 1.0
Setter: set_vrs_strength(value: float)
Getter: get_vrs_strength() -> float
The strength used to calculate the VRS density map. The greater this value, the more noticeable VRS is. This improves performance at the cost of quality.
Note: Mobile and Forward+ renderers only. Requires Viewport.vrs_mode to be set to Viewport.VRS_XR.